<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="461" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1567,1952]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1748,1773]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from the 
<typeStatus box="[734,832,1748,1773]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">holotype</typeStatus>
(male) and one male 
<typeStatus box="[1075,1171,1749,1773]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">paratype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectionCode box="[1240,1323,1748,1772]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">GUGC</collectionCode>
. It closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Nielson, 1977" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="1977" box="[270,564,1783,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obrienae">
<emphasis box="[270,399,1783,1808]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">T. obrienae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson" box="[406,564,1783,1808]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1977) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) II. Tribe Thagriini. Pacific Insects Monograph, 34, 1 - 218." type="journal article" year="1977">
Nielson, 
<quantity box="[508,564,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.02158" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" unit="in" value="1977.0">1977</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, but differs in having the pygofer processes exceeding the ventral margin of the pygofer lobe and with the apex pointed, and the ventral processes of segment X serrate (
<figureCitation box="[159,322,1855,1880]" captionStart="FIGURES 109 – 118" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[198,1396,198,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[189,1400,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 109 – 118. Thagria furcata. 109. habitus, dorsal view; 110. habitus, lateral view; 111. head and thorax, dorsal view; 112. face; 113. pygofer and segment X ventral process, lateral view; 114. dorsal connective, pygofer and segment X processes, dorsal view; 115. subgential plate, lateral view; 116. aedeagus, paraphysis, connective and style, dorsal view; 117. aedeagus and paraphysis, lateral view; 118. style, lateral view. Scale bars: 109 – 112 = 1.0 mm; 113 – 118 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253929/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
Figs. 
<number box="[222,322,1856,1880]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="113.114">113, 114</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName box="[372,500,1855,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obrienae">
<emphasis box="[372,500,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">T. obrienae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pygofer processes do not reach the ventral margin of the pygofer lobe, the apex is truncate, and the ventral processes of segment X have the margins smooth, without tooth (
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1977) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) II. Tribe Thagriini. Pacific Insects Monograph, 34, 1 - 218." type="journal article" year="1977">
Nielson 
<number box="[1328,1388,1892,1916]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="1977.0">1977</number>
: 
<number box="[1401,1431,1892,1917]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" value="55.0">55</number>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,315,1927,1952]" captionStart="FIGURES 153 – 163" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1889,1912]" captionTargetBox="[209,1386,196,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[204,1388,193,1865]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 153 – 163. Thagria multispinosa Fan &amp; Dai, sp. nov. Holotype: 153. habitus, dorsal view; 154. habitus, lateral view; 155. head and thorax, dorsal view; 156. face; 157. pygofer, lateral view; 158. subgential plate, lateral view; 159. dorsal connective, dorsal view; 160. aedeagus, paraphysis, connective and style, dorsal view; 161. aedeagus and paraphysis, lateral view; 162. apex of right style, lateral view; 163. apex of left style, lateral view. Scale bars: 153 – 156 = 1.0 mm; 157 – 163 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253933/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
